{
  "doc_id": "17521",
  "text": "Confirmation of the diagnosis requires either enzyme assay or mutation analysis. FAH assays may be performed on liver biopsy, fibroblasts, lymphocytes or dried blood spots [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Falsely elevated enzyme results may be obtained on liver biopsy if a reverted nodule is inadvertently assayed. Enzyme assay results should therefore be interpreted in the context of the patients' clinical and biochemical findings.",
